Installation instructions for ParaDe 2 (26/07/2007):

1) Get a Tomcat version and extract it into the folder tomcat-fresh
2) Make sure you have a MySQL server running on port 3306 with an empty database called "parade".
   The settings can be changed in webapp/WEB-INF/classes/hibernate.cfg.xml if needed
3) Check if the server.xml in tomcat/conf corresponds to your tomcat version
4) Run the install script: sh install.sh
5) That's it! You should be able to run ParaDe by launching the tomcat.sh script in the directory tomcat-parade
6) The rows.properties file will be created in the WEB-INF/classes directory, edit it to add new rows
